The paper deals with computational complexity and algorithms for problems related to sets and relations, which are common topics in computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on the complexity of computing minimal unidirectional covering sets, which is a problem that can be formulated in terms of data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), game theory (cs.GT), and logic (cs.LO).
